      "writtenOn": "2026-05-01T01:57:31Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The app uses hash history, But the `Login.vue` code reads the browser URL search params directly:\n```\n            const url \u003d new URL(window.location.href);\n            const nextPath \u003d url.searchParams.get(\u0027next\u0027);\n            this.handleNextPathRedirect(nextPath);\n```\n\nThis does not work for for hash-router URLs like /#/login?next\u003d/redfish/v1/..., where window.location.search is empty and the query is available through this.$route.query.next.\n\nRecommended fix: use Vue Router query first, then fall back to window.location.search for bmcweb-style redirects:\n```\nconst nextPath \u003d\n  this.$route.query.next ||\n  new URL(window.location.href).searchParams.get(\u0027next\u0027);\n```",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 9,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 11,
        "endChar": 9
      },
      "revId": "600d87fa10a8941319d17089ee24eda6a3a09eb8",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
