      "side": 1,
      "message": "while it makes sense that the Login component is special, it seems like we can centralize redirect logic (similar logic is needed in the router for `/login`.\n\nConsider adding one safe helper and use it both from the router and the Login.vue:\n```\nfunction isRedfishRedirectPath(path) {\n  return path \u003d\u003d\u003d \u0027/redfish/v1\u0027 || path?.startsWith(\u0027/redfish/v1/\u0027);\n}\n\nfunction redirectToRedfishOrHome(path, router) {\n  if (isRedfishRedirectPath(path)) {\n    window.location.assign(`${window.location.origin}${path}`);\n  } else {\n    router.push(\u0027/\u0027);\n  }\n}\n```\n\nplace within router or in a Redfish utility.",
